column1: 81060;instagram;2019-01-01 17:50:55;FALSE;"â€œi forgive the world. the world forgives me. and i forgive myself.â€
this was one of the first mantras that i received from my spiritual director as i began my healing journey. forgiveness is never about the other person. and in my case
column2: it was about taking my power back and putting an end to the pattern of abuse that was keeping me in the victim role. part of stepping into my power also required me to forgive myself. we all react differently in threatening situations
column3: so blaming ourselves for our choice to stay in the cycle of abuse is pointless. i had to release the shame and guilt i was carrying around like a weighted backpack.

column1: 81143;instagram;2019-01-11 05:24:03;FALSE;"we should all be feminists! it's about equality not what you should or shouldn't be but what you want to be. if you want to be an independent woman who is single go do that! if you want to be a mom and a wife
column2: do that! if you want to shave
column4: then don't. be who you want to be! i'm tired of the division i see among women. i am saddened by the people and women who bash the #metoo movement. those who claim we are just ""weak"" or ""pansies"" or that we need to grow up and realize lifes not fair?? excuse my language but wtf? grow up? how is it we live in a world where sexual abuse is not taken seriously? that the victim is at fault? or that men/boys sexually abused should enjoy it because it's a woman and if they don't like it they must not be a man? personal space is personal space. consent is consent. no means no. we are not a generation that is weak
column5: we are a generation that is not afraid. i won't pretend the old ways were better because they were not! change is happening with or without the permission of everyone who believes we need to go back to the ways things used to be. i highly recommend everyone watch ""on the basis of sex"". it sparked a fire in me. if i seem mad or upset it's because i am. i will let those emotions fuel me to fight for change. women deserve equality. sexual assault victims deserve to be heard! despite race
column7: and more! i'm a feminist and we all should be!

column1: 81185;instagram;2019-01-11 00:01:13;FALSE;"we are joining the womyns wave! femme fatale is hosting a pre-march diy ""no"" tees meetup jan. 17 7-9pm. the #womensmarch exists to fight bigotry and discrimination in all their forms and to lift up the voices of womyn who are too often left out. join us in unity for an evening of creating no tee to show your support in dismantling aspects of society that are harmful to the human race. this is a safe space and we invite you to join in a conversation or share your stories of inequality and injustices. supplies for womyn march signs + tees will be available.
about the creator of the no tees:

column4: is inspired by her disdain for the fact that men + womyn are treated so disproportionately. the #inequality
column7: #catcalling + general unsolicited comments by male counterparts based on appearance or gender are a real + daunting part of being a womyn. no tees was an expression of her taking back her voice + saying no to aspects of society that are harmful with hopes of sparking conversations to make spaces safer for womyn as well as all people who are victimized due to inequalities + #injustices -

column1: @farymahh will also be sharing the work she hopes to see done at all #dmv airports as well as her experience as an permanent resident in amerikkka.
all supplies included. prosecco will also be on deck!!! +feel free to byob/t.
red brick carriage house alley of the 1200 block of florida ave ne & trinidad ave ne

leaving at all â˜ºï¸ the universe has truly blessed me!!! the word inspirational will not even cut how absolutely unbelievably moving and powerful these last 10 months have been. last april, i was asked by a friend (emily dawson) to help her form the first sexual assault survivors anonymous group in the united states of america. this experience has changed me forever. the power of healing, hope and joy has been so deep rooted in my soul, truly beyond honored to be a part of this movement. proud to say i have acted as the cofounder and attended all of our meetings every thursday from may to november of 2018. the men and women and i have connected with will always have the strongest impact on my heart and soul. i love you all with every bit of my heart and soul. thank you for the support received from my friends and loved ones and total strangers. this amazing experience has led me to become an advocate for sexual assault and domestic violence. i hope that i can continue to help other survivors find the healing and help they need. and will continue to advocate and have a voice for everyone who suffers in silence. thank you all so much for being supportive and giving me more help than i could ever imagine for my healing journey. never forget that there are people here who love you and only want the best for you. there are professionals always willing to help! i am willing to help! i love you, i believe you and i want you to be happy and safe! there are professionals and people who will always believe you and want the best for you! there are wonderful people who want you column1: i hate bringing race into things but on this i see no other factor for the blatant cherry picking of when we decide enough is enough .

i think we as a society can and should acknowledge when a person does something criminal or reprehensible but to remove them from the history books per se does no one any good .
this is my view and opinion to which you don't have to agree .

column3: awlo in collaboration with rwanda convention bureau will be converging for the 11th african women in leadership conference (awlc)

column2: all delegates and stakeholders will sit down together to formulate solutions for women's empowerment issues in africa.

column1: the conference will also showcase 5 enterprising african women; who will tell their story

column2: professionals and leaders to further advance the leadership status of women in the continent of africa.

column1: i got flowers today. it wasn't my birthday or any other special day. we had our first argument last night. he said a lot of cruel things that really hurt me. i know he was sorry and didn't mean the things he said. because i got flowers today.
i got flowers today. it wasn't our anniversary or any other special day. last night
column2: he threw me into a wall and started to choke me. it seemed like a nightmare. i couldn't believe it was real. i woke up this morning sore and bruised all over. i know he must be sorry because he sent me flowers today.

column1: i got flowers today. it wasn't mother's day or any other special day. last night
column2: he beat me up again. and it was much worse than all other times. if i leave him
column3: what will i do? how will i take care of my kids? what about money? i' m afraid of him and scared to leave. but i know he must be sorry because he sent me flowers today.

column1: i got flowers today. today was a very special day. it was the day of my funeral. last night he finally killed me. he beat me to death.
if only i had gathered enough courage and strength to leave him
column2: i would not have gotten flowers today.

column1: 81675;instagram;2019-01-10 21:44:35;FALSE;#tbt i was 10 in these photos we had just moved from vallejo to napa. because my dad had a heart attack a triple bypass! i saw him having his heart attack itâ€™s was the scariest thing. little did he know his heart attack saved me from my predator! i was being molested by my babysitters son every school day! after pretending to be sick (quickly learned that didnâ€™t work) i thought my mom would stay home to take care of me. instead she still took me there! so i started getting in trouble at school to get detention. that worked out i got to stay at school till it was almost time to be picked up. finally one day i got the courage to tell my mom. unfortunately she didnâ€™t really seem to believe me or care. she just told the sitter to keep her son away from me. if you could only imagine the pain everyday i faced on the drive there. i started to wish we would get in a car accident or maybe i would just die. it just occurred to me recently she never told my dad she just pretended like it never happened. i never got any help or treatment for what happened to me. it has greatly effected my adult life! i have let ppl treat me less than all my life! never sticking up for myself! unfortunately it took me hitting rock bottom for me to see how iâ€™ve let ppl walk all over me! this year is all about me healing and putting myself 1st! i will no longer let anyone treat me less than ever again!!!! you will never put words in my mouth or ever throw any accusations at me ever!!! #iamtakingastand #imatter #metoo #puttingmefirst #youcanttreatmelessthan #iwillstandupformyself #iamstrong #fighting #demons #selfawareness #selfcare #icandoit #youcantbreakme #mylife #mychoice #ichooseme #idecidewhoiwillspendmytimewith #mykids #theyaremyworld #mysourceofstrength #happiness #love #myeverything #iwillalwaysbethere #iwillfightforyou #iwillneverletyoudown #iloveyou #youwillalwaysbemybabies #forever;;en;#tbt

column1: gonna get serious for a second...
2018 was a big year for a lot of reasons but the one that stuck out most for me was our surge to fight sexual violence.

this picture was taken just as i was reading out the news bulletin on brett kavanaugh's appointment onto the supreme court. watching christine blasey ford share her truth on a global stage was one of the bravest things i've ever seen.
it was one of many events this year that inspired me to finally take the first step in addressing some of my experiences of sexual violence.
it was the year i recognised past abusers. it was the year i fully forgave myself and said fuck you to anyone who felt i should keep hush hush about my experiences.
so many people have made that choice and more will
column2: and more and more until we can finally say goodbye to the stigma surrounding topics of sexual violence + so much more!

column1: we are done hiding in the shadows and shutting up about unpleasant subjects to make everyone more comfortable.

column6: emotional and physical abuse have all persisted because we kept it tucked away in the shadows.

column2: on the morning of 19th december my mum ran on me room in tears she told me the ambulance was on it's way and that my step dad
column3: my farther figure the best person to have ever came in to my life has had a major stroke. my heart sank it felt like it has been shattered in to a million peaceâ€™s. my dad is still in hospital to this day
column4: it hurts so much to see him this way. most people wish of fancy holidays and all the luxuries but not me my wish is just to actually be able to have a conversation with my dad and it's painful so so painful to no that it may never happen
column5: itâ€™s painful not knowing when we will have him home with us
column6: having to watch him and help him learn everything all over again.
